Cascadia Emergency Department Quarterly Report

June, 2021

\(~\) \(~\)

Every small change adds up to reduce avoidable emergency department (ED)
visits among our clients

Data from Collective Medical were combined with Cascadia EHR data to determine information on emergency department (ED) utilization from Jan-June. Information presented includes Cascadia clients with an ROI for Collective Medical, who utilized the ED at least once in the past 12 months.

\(~\) \(~\) \(~\)

Data on emergency department utilization

trends, year-to-date


As of June 9, 2021 there have been 7276 emergency department visits across all Cascadia Behavioral Health Care clients.




Between May 1st to May 31st, 28.1% of clients had two or more ED visits.


Of our clients with at least one visit in May, 22.9% had 5-9 visits in the past year, and 21.8% had 10 or more visits.

Emergency Department Utilization by Client Characteristics





Emergency department visits and rates of higher levels of emergency department utilization vary by client-level characteristics







Housing status is a significant predictor or emergency department visit numbers and trends




Percentage of clients with more frequent ED utilization patterns is consistently

higher for clients who are unhoused compared to clients who are housed
